      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "name": "Black Pepper",
      "amount": "1/4 teaspoon",
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "name": "Feta Cheese (optional)",
      "amount": "1/2 cup",
      "notes": "crumbled, dairy-free alternative for Whole30"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 425°F (220°C).",
    "Slice the Chinese long beans into 1-inch pieces and place them on a baking sheet. ",
    "Drizzle with olive oil and toss to coat.",
    "Sprinkle garlic, dried oregano, salt, and black pepper over the beans and toss again to coat.",
    "Roast in the preheated oven for 20 minutes, or until the beans start to brown.",
    "While the beans are roasting, mix together pickle slices and feta cheese (if using). ",
    "Once the beans are done roasting, remove them from the oven and top each bean with the pickle-feta mixture.",
    "Return the baking sheet to the oven and continue baking for an additional 5-7 minutes, or until the topping is lightly browned.",
    "Serve hot and enjoy!"
  ],
